        "description": "Over years I worked across many teams within Facebook Infrastructure org. I generally act as a hands-on TL.\n\nSome highlights:\n* Led re-architecture of data reading and pre-processing infrastructure used primarily for RecSys training.  Focusing on making the infra \"invisible\" while meeting growing scale and efficiency demands.\n* Worked towards unifying all in-datacenter RPC workloads on Thrift. This was achieved through adding new capabilities (e.g. streaming), 10x performance improvements in the Thrift transport and replacing network protocol with RSocket (https://rsocket.io/).\n* Drove upgrade of Facebook's C++ codebase to use C++ coroutines making Facebook one of the largest (or maybe even the largest ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯ ) C++ coroutines users in the world. Designed libraries and process to enable mostly organic adoption.\n* Either author or key contributor of many core C++ libraries used at Facebook: folly::coro, folly::fibers, folly::futures, folly::observer, folly::Singleton and more. See https://github.com/facebook/folly\n* Led the migration of all Instagram graph metadata (likes, posts etc.) from PostgreSQL to Facebook's graph database (TAO).",
